<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id52a2446a-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s1354"><num value="1354">§ 1354.</num><heading> Land grants from different states</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The district courts shall have original jurisdiction of actions between citizens of the same state claiming lands under grants from different states.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id52a2446b-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646">June 25, 1948, ch. 646</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/934">62 Stat. 934</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id52a2446c-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id52a2446d-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 41(1) (<ref href="/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s24">Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 24</ref>, par. 1, <ref href="/us/stat/36/1091">36 Stat. 1091</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1934-05-14/ch283/s1">May 14, 1934, ch. 283, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/48/775">48 Stat. 775</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1937-08-21/ch726/s1">Aug. 21, 1937, ch. 726, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/50/738">50 Stat. 738</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1940-04-20/ch117">Apr. 20, 1940, ch. 117</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/54/143">54 Stat. 143</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Other provisions of <ref href="/us/usc/t28/s41/1">section 41(1) of title 28</ref>, U.S.C., 1940 ed., are incorporated in sections 1331, 1332, 1341, 1342, 1345, and 1359 of this title.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Changes were made in phraseology.</p>
</note>
